<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AFC 00906 - Replacement of CabMate Suspension Lower Crossmember Mounting Bracket in 9000i Pro Sleeper Models
        Built in Chatham Between February 1, 2000 and April 10, 2000, and Escobedo Between February 1, 2000 and May 2,
        2000.
    </stitle>
    <afc id="afc00906">
        <afcnum>00906</afcnum>
        <afcdate>June, 2000</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>CAB</subjectfile>
        <subject>Replacement of CabMate Suspension Lower Crossmember Mounting Bracket in 9000i Pro Sleeper Models Built
            in Chatham Between February 1, 2000 and April 10, 2000, and Escobedo Between February 1, 2000 and May 2,
            2000.
        </subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9000i
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>02/01/2000</startdate>
                        <enddate>05/02/2000</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The passenger side CabMate suspension air spring (bag) may have interference with the crossmember
                    mounting bracket. If this interference occurs the air spring (bag) can fail and result in a harsh
                    ride. To repair or prevent this failure the CabMate suspension lower crossmember mounting bracket
                    must be replaced.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
