        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="4">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>This Authorized Field Change does not cover the replacement of the air springs unless the
                        rubber sleeve is worn enough for the internal cords to be visible. Air Springs with light scuff
                        marks are satisfactory and not covered.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>The CabMate suspension lot numbers, located on the id tag (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0090601">Figure 1</hotlnk>) involved in this Authorized Field Change are: 4770,
                        4800, 4817, 4826, 4839, 4850, 4862, 4876, 4894, 4906, 4927, 4939, 4953, and 4968.
                    </para>
                    <para>Any lot numbers with an " X" suffix have been reworked with the new crossmember mounting
                        bracket at the assembly plant (i.e., lot number 4939 becomes 4939X after rework).
                        <emph type="bold">These suspensions do not require rework.</emph>
                    </para>
                    <para>Visually inspect the crossmember mounting bracket and compare it to
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0090602">Figure 2</hotlnk>
                        before proceeding. Only the original bracket (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0090602">Figure 2</hotlnk>) is affected by this Authorized Field Change.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f0090601" figsize="pg-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0090601.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                                 resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. Lot Number Tag Location</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f0090602" figsize="pg-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0090602.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                                 resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2. Original vs Current or Replacement Bracket Comparison</caption>
                    </figure>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Apply the parking brakes and chock the tires to prevent possible property damage, personal
                        injury, or death.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise the cab and block it about 1 inch higher than design height.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reduce the system air pressure to 0 PSI.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0090603">Figure 3</hotlnk>
                    for the following Steps.
                </emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="f0090603" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0090603.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Reference for Removal Steps</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the pivot ball from the crossmember mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the lever down to exhaust all air pressure from both air springs.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shock absorber mounting bolt from the crossmember mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the lateral control rod mounting bolt from the crossmember mounting bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grasp the air springs by hand and turn them counterclockwise several times until they
                    are free from the captive mounting fasteners.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the mounting fasteners that hold the crossmember mounting bracket to the
                    crossmember.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the crossmember mounting bracket from the crossmember and install the new
                    crossmember mounting bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosely install the lateral control rod to the new crossmember mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosely install the shock absorbers to the new crossmember mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the air springs to the new crossmember mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new crossmember mounting bracket to the crossmember. Tighten the fasteners
                    to 30 to 38 Ft-lbs. (41 to 52 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the lateral control rod mounting fasteners to 70 to 90 Ft-lbs. (95 to 122 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the shock absorber mounting fasteners to 40 to 50 Ft-lbs. (54 to 68 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the pivot ball to the new crossmember mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise the cab and remove the block installed in Step 2.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start the engine to build up system pressure and verify the air spring design height is
                    6.5 inches. Adjust valve linkage if necessary (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0090604">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0090604" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0090604.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Design Height Measurement</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
